1. Purchase organic soil and other fertilizers that are sustainably-sourced and in compliance with local organic regulations;
2. Use compost, natural mulch, and/or integrated pest management practices to reduce waste or need for artificial inputs;
3. Use rainwater collection systems, cisterns or a watershed approach to manage irrigation needs; 
4. Plant native species whenever possible to reduce maintenance needs; 
5. Make use of vertical gardening systems and grow lights when necessary in order to maximize production in limited spaces; 
6. Utilize repurposed materials including plastic barrels and containers, old buckets/barrel seats from construction sites, and discarded food packaging (cardboard boxes) as containers for different plants - making sure to properly cleaned prior use
